"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-08-usa-rally-beat-serbia-reach-olympic-mens-basketball-final\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS, France (AFP) - The United States erased a 17-point deficit to beat Nikola Jokic's Serbia 95-91 on Thusday and reach the Olympic men's basketball final, keeping their bid for a fifth straight gold medal alive.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 215, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9935975702207477, \"rank\": 0.006443519964560356, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 26, \"end\": 39, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0426275178741315e-16, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 74, \"end\": 86, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Joki\\u0107\", \"score\": 0.9999999949418452, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nikola Jokic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Joki\\u0107\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Joki\\u0107\"}, {\"begin\": 89, \"end\": 95, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9816187680344238, \"rank\": 0.01870117097886594, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Golden State Warriors star Stephen Curry dazzled with 36 points and all-time NBA scoring leader LeBron James had a triple-double of 16 points, 12 rebounds and 10 assists.\", \"from\": 217, \"to\": 387, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 217, \"end\": 238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golden_State_Warriors\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9633759004907527e-56, \"text\": \"Golden State Warriors\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golden_State_Warriors\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golden_State_Warriors\"}, {\"begin\": 244, \"end\": 257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7245582419332007e-47, \"text\": \"Stephen Curry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\"}, {\"begin\": 313, \"end\": 325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LeBron James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it took a massive fourth-quarter effort to finally subdue the Serbs, who led most of the night and took a 76-63 advantage into the fourth quarter.\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 455, \"end\": 460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbs\", \"score\": 0.9677369361515501, \"rank\": 0.028250529682905662, \"text\": \"Serbs\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbs\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kevin Durant and Devin Booker drilled back-to-back three-pointers to start the fight-back.\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 547, \"end\": 553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0684364826860997e-29, \"text\": \"Durant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_Durant\"}, {\"begin\": 558, \"end\": 570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Devin_Booker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.308822105450003e-47, \"text\": \"Devin Booker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Devin_Booker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Devin_Booker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Joel Embiid pulled the States within four with a three-point play and James tied it up at 84-84 with 3:41 to play.\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 747, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 633, \"end\": 644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Joel Embiid\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joel_Embiid\"}, {\"begin\": 703, \"end\": 708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7294066497235516e-27, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Curry rattled in a three-pointer with 2:24 remaining to give the United States their first lead since the first quarter 87-87.\", \"from\": 749, \"to\": 875, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 814, \"end\": 827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0426275178741315e-16, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"James followed with a driving layup, Curry grabbed a steal and drove for a basket that pushed the US lead to five and the Americans held on.\", \"from\": 877, \"to\": 1017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7294066497235516e-27, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 975, \"end\": 977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.608968997647895e-18, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Embiid scored 19 points and Durant woke up just in time after a sleepy first half to add nine as the US kept their bid for a 17th Olympic title alive.\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1120, \"end\": 1122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.608968997647895e-18, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three-time NBA Most Valuable Player Jokic finished with 17 points and 11 assists for Serbia, who got 20 points from a brilliant Bogdan Bogdanovic.\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1317, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1182, \"end\": 1185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.872440880051798e-32, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1256, \"end\": 1262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9816187680344238, \"rank\": 0.01870117097886594, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1299, \"end\": 1316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bogdan_Bogdanovi\\u0107_(basketball)\", \"score\": 0.9999999927240424, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bogdan Bogdanovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bogdan_Bogdanovi\\u0107_(basketball)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bogdan_Bogdanovi\\u0107_(basketball)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Curry got off to a scorching start, drilling five three-pointers on the way to 17 first-quarter points.\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1422, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But Serbia combined for five three-pointers themselves and led 31-23 after a frenetic first quarter in which only four players scored for the United States.\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1580, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1428, \"end\": 1434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9816187680344238, \"rank\": 0.01870117097886594, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1566, \"end\": 1579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0426275178741315e-16, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Serbia continued to pour it on, pushing their lead to 42-25 with more than six minutes left in the second period.\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1582, \"end\": 1588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9816187680344238, \"rank\": 0.01870117097886594, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Struggling offensively, the United States were also unable to slow the Serbian offense keyed by Jokic.\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1725, \"end\": 1738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0426275178741315e-16, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1768, \"end\": 1775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbian_language\", \"score\": 0.4993546227732542, \"rank\": 0.6813000157284473, \"text\": \"Serbian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbian_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aleksa Avramovic was a deadly four-of-six from three-point range on the way to 15 first-half points and Atlanta Hawks shooting guard Bogdanovic had 12 before the break.\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1969, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1801, \"end\": 1807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksa_\\u0110ura\\u0161evi\\u0107\", \"score\": 0.454999991887014, \"rank\": 0.8131868131867451, \"text\": \"Aleksa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksa_\\u0110ura\\u0161evi\\u0107\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksa_\\u0110ura\\u0161evi\\u0107\"}, {\"begin\": 1905, \"end\": 1918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta_Hawks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.76847995014081e-52, \"text\": \"Atlanta Hawks\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta_Hawks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta_Hawks\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Curry had 20 points in the first half but subdued Phoenix Suns star Durant missed his only attempt.\", \"from\": 1971, \"to\": 2070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2021, \"end\": 2033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Suns\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.995461615924196e-54, \"text\": \"Phoenix Suns\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Suns\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Phoenix_Suns\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Suddenly the United States, whose romp through the group stage incuded a 110-84 victory over Serbia, looked in serious trouble for the first time at the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 2072, \"to\": 2237, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2085, \"end\": 2098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0426275178741315e-16, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2165, \"end\": 2171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9816187680344238, \"rank\": 0.01870117097886594, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back-to-back three-pointers from Curry and Jrue Holiday cut the deficit to 59-65 but try as they might the US could not reel Serbia in.\", \"from\": 2239, \"to\": 2374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2346, \"end\": 2348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.608968997647895e-18, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2364, \"end\": 2370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9816187680344238, \"rank\": 0.01870117097886594, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marko Guduric converted a four-point play when he was fouled by Derrick White on a bomb from well beyond the arc to propel Serbia into the fourth quarter in the ascent.\", \"from\": 2376, \"to\": 2544, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2440, \"end\": 2453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derrick_White_(basketball)\", \"score\": 0.9925925345590776, \"rank\": 0.006633499170812927, \"text\": \"Derrick White\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derrick_White_(basketball)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derrick_White_(basketball)\"}, {\"begin\": 2499, \"end\": 2505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9816187680344238, \"rank\": 0.01870117097886594, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the US team, reckoned to be the most talented since Michael Jordan led the 1992 Dream Team, found a way.\", \"from\": 2546, \"to\": 2654, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2554, \"end\": 2556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.608968997647895e-18, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2602, \"end\": 2616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jordan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.10687774444244e-43, \"text\": \"Michael Jordan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jordan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Jordan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tags:  HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 2674, \"entities\": []}]}"